{"declarations":[{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Linter/Extra/DupNamespace.html#Lean.Linter.Extra.DupNamespaceLinter.dupNamespace\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Linter</span>.<span class=\"name\">Extra</span>.<span class=\"name\">DupNamespaceLinter</span>.<span class=\"name\">dupNamespace</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Command.html#Lean.Elab.Command.Linter\">Linter</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The `dupNamespace` linter is set off by default.  Lean emits a warning on any declaration that\ncontains the same namespace more than once.\n\nBy default, only consecutive duplication is reported: `Nat.Nat.foo` and `One.two.two` trigger a\nwarning, while `Nat.One.Nat` does not. Setting `linter.extra.dupNamespace.consecutiveOnly` to\n`false` also reports non-consecutive duplication, so that `Nat.One.Nat` triggers a warning as well.\n","docLink":"./Lean/Linter/Extra/DupNamespace.html#Lean.Linter.Extra.DupNamespaceLinter.dupNamespace","kind":"def","line":75,"name":"Lean.Linter.Extra.DupNamespaceLinter.dupNamespace","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Linter/Extra/DupNamespace.lean#L75-L102"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Linter/Extra/DupNamespace.html#Lean.Linter.Extra.DupNamespaceLinter.getAliasSyntax\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Linter</span>.<span class=\"name\">Extra</span>.<span class=\"name\">DupNamespaceLinter</span>.<span class=\"name\">getAliasSyntax</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">m</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> → <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a></span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Monad\">Monad</a> <span class=\"fn\">m</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/ResolveName.html#Lean.MonadResolveName\">MonadResolveName</a> <span class=\"fn\">m</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">stx</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.Syntax\">Syntax</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">m</span> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Array\">Array</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.Syntax\">Syntax</a>)</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"If `stx` is a syntax node for an `export` statement, then `getAliasSyntax stx` returns the array of\nidentifiers with the \"exported\" names.\n","docLink":"./Lean/Linter/Extra/DupNamespace.html#Lean.Linter.Extra.DupNamespaceLinter.getAliasSyntax","kind":"def","line":61,"name":"Lean.Linter.Extra.DupNamespaceLinter.getAliasSyntax","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Linter/Extra/DupNamespace.lean#L61-L73"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Linter/Extra/DupNamespace.html#Lean.Linter.Extra.DupNamespaceLinter.getNamesFrom\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Linter</span>.<span class=\"name\">Extra</span>.<span class=\"name\">DupNamespaceLinter</span>.<span class=\"name\">getNamesFrom</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">m</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> → <a href=\"./foundational_ty